<grammar_tables title="Early accent/ablaut classes (Beekes)">
    <description>The early development of the PIE accent/ablaut classes as read into <source book="Beekes1985" /> (incomplete). Classes are written out in the form "[root ablaut]-[suffix ablaut]-[case marker ablaut]", with an accent put on top of an ablaut known to be stressed. The order of tables is not strictly chronological, but rather analytical: Beekes often specifies the order of steps only vaguely, or as happening roughly at the same developmental stage, without going into detail about their relative order. For reasons of clarity, I decided to introduce such steps in separate tables of a certain order, even if they may have happened in parallel, or in a slightly different order.</description>
    <grammar_table id="I" title="Stage I: static/mobile, accent stage" short_title="stage I">
        <description>The fundamental difference between inflections is static/mobile. The initial ablaut stage is the "zero phase" (p. 157): only the accented vowel is non-zero. This stage is equal to stage I in the p. 207 table.</description>
        <declension_def id="static" title="static" short_title="static" />
        <declension_def id="mobile" title="mobile" short_title="mobile" />
        <case_def id="all" title="all cases">
            <case_def id="A" title="absolutive" short_title="absolutive" />
            <case_def id="L" title="locative" short_title="locative" />
        </case_def>
        <paradigm declension="static" case="all" form="e00" footnote="I_static" />
        <paradigm declension="mobile" case="A" form="e00" footnote="I_mobile_absolutive" />
        <paradigm declension="mobile" case="L" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
    </grammar_table>
    <grammar_table id="II" title="Stage II: mobile ergative" short_title="stage II">
        <description>Various case markers append to the locative inflection – as per p. 202, 207: directive -m, dative -i, instrumental -h₁, genitive-ablative -s (unaccented) and -ós (accented). The (ergative) genitive-ablative gets its own paradigm in the mobile inflection. This stage is equal to stage II in the p. 207 table.</description>
        <declension_def id="static" title="static" short_title="static" />
        <declension_def id="mobile" title="mobile" short_title="mobile" />
        <case_def id="all" title="all cases">
            <case_def id="Abs" title="absolutive" short_title="absolutive" />
            <case_def id="L+Da+Di+I" title="locative, dative, directive, instrumental">
                <case_def id="Di" title="directive" short_title="directive" />
                <case_def id="L" title="locative" short_title="locative" />
                <case_def id="I" title="instrumental" short_title="instrumental" />
                <case_def id="Da" title="dative" short_title="dative" />
            </case_def>
            <case_def id="G+Abl" title="genitive-ablative" short_title="genitive-ablative" />
        </case_def>
        <paradigm declension="static" case="all" form="e00" footnote="I_static" />
        <paradigm declension="mobile" case="Abs" form="e00" footnote="I_mobile_absolutive" />
        <paradigm declension="mobile" case="L+Da+Di+I" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
        <paradigm declension="mobile" case="G+Abl" form="00o" footnote="II_mobile_genitive-ablative" />
    </grammar_table>
    <grammar_table id="III/IV" title="Stage III/IV: proterodynamic/hysterodynamic" short_title="stage III/IV">
        <description>Ergativity and gender split the mobile inflection (p. 171, 203): In animate (hysterodynamic) nouns, the case marker accent of the ergative genitive-ablative is extended. In non-ergative inanimate (proterodynamic) nouns, the genitive-ablative loses its case marker accent to other cases' suffix accent. This stage lies somewhere between stages III and IV in the p. 207 table.</description>
        <declension_def id="static" title="static" short_title="static" />
        <declension_def id="mobile" title="mobile">
            <declension_def id="PD" title="proterodynamic/neuter" short_title="PD (n)" />
            <declension_def id="HD" title="hysterodynamic/animate" short_title="HD (mf)" />
        </declension_def>
        <case_def id="all" title="all">
            <case_def id="Abs" title="absolutive" short_title="absolutive" />
            <case_def id="Di+L+I" title="directive, locative">
                <case_def id="Di" title="directive" short_title="directive" />
                <case_def id="L" title="locative" short_title="locative" />
                <case_def id="I" title="instrumental" short_title="instrumental" />
            </case_def>
            <case_def id="Da" title="dative" short_title="dative" />
            <case_def id="G+Abl" title="genitive-ablative" short_title="genitive-ablative" />
        </case_def>
        <paradigm declension="static" case="all" form="e00" footnote="I_static" />
        <paradigm declension="mobile" case="Abs" form="e00" footnote="I_mobile_absolutive" />
        <paradigm declension="mobile" case="Di+L+I" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="Da" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="G+Abl" form="0e0" footnote="III/IV_pd_genitive-ablative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="Da" form="00e" footnote="III/IV_hd_dative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="G+Abl" form="00o" footnote="II_mobile_genitive-ablative" />
    </grammar_table>
    <grammar_table id="IV" title="Stage IV: nominative/accusative" short_title="stage IV">
        <description>The ergative system is replaced by a nominative system. The absolutive becomes the nominative. The ergative's function of highlighting the subject of an action against its object is taken over by the accusative highlighting the object against the (nominative) subject. This differentiation only happens in the formerly ergative hysterodynamic inflection, where the directive becomes the accusative. In the proterodynamic inflection, the former absolutive also becomes the accusative. This stage is equal to parts of stage IV in the p. 207 table.</description>
        <declension_def id="static" title="static" short_title="static" />
        <declension_def id="mobile" title="mobile">
            <declension_def id="PD" title="proterodynamic/neuter" short_title="PD (n)" />
            <declension_def id="HD" title="hysterodynamic/animate" short_title="HD (mf)" />
        </declension_def>
        <case_def id="all" title="all">
            <case_def id="N" title="nominative" short_title="nominative" />
            <case_def id="Ac" title="accusative" short_title="accusative" />
            <case_def id="L+I" title="locative, instrumental">
                <case_def id="L" title="locative" short_title="locative" />
                <case_def id="I" title="instrumental" short_title="instrumental" />
            </case_def>
            <case_def id="Da" title="dative" short_title="dative" />
            <case_def id="G+Abl" title="genitive-ablative" short_title="genitive-ablative" />
        </case_def>
        <paradigm declension="static" case="all" form="e00" footnote="I_static" />
        <paradigm declension="mobile" case="N" form="e00" footnote="IV_mobile_nominative" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="Ac" form="e00" footnote="IV_pd_accusative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="Ac" form="0e0" footnote="IV_hd_accusative" />
        <paradigm declension="mobile" case="L+I" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="Da" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="G+Abl" form="0e0" footnote="III/IV_pd_genitive-ablative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="Da" form="00e" footnote="III/IV_hd_dative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="G+Abl" form="00o" footnote="II_mobile_genitive-ablative" />
    </grammar_table>
    <grammar_table id="IV/Va" title="Stage IV/V (a): o-stems" short_title="stage IV/Va">
        <description>A new inflection emerges (p. 192) from the ergative genitive's Ø-Ø-ó class: the o-stems. This stage lies somewhere between stages IV and V in the p. 207 table.</description>
        <declension_def id="static" title="static" short_title="static" />
        <declension_def id="mobile" title="mobile">
            <declension_def id="PD" title="proterodynamic/neuter" short_title="PD (n)" />
            <declension_def id="HD" title="hysterodynamic/animate" short_title="HD (mf)" />
        </declension_def>
        <declension_def id="O" title="o-stems" short_title="O" />
        <case_def id="all" title="all">
            <case_def id="N" title="nominative" short_title="nominative" />
            <case_def id="Ac" title="accusative" short_title="accusative" />
            <case_def id="L+I" title="locative, instrumental">
                <case_def id="L" title="locative" short_title="locative" />
                <case_def id="I" title="instrumental" short_title="instrumental" />
            </case_def>
            <case_def id="Da" title="dative" short_title="dative" />
            <case_def id="G+Abl" title="genitive-ablative" short_title="genitive-ablative" />
        </case_def>
        <paradigm declension="static" case="all" form="e00" footnote="I_static" />
        <paradigm declension="mobile" case="N" form="e00" footnote="IV_mobile_nominative" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="Ac" form="e00" footnote="IV_pd_accusative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="Ac" form="0e0" footnote="IV_hd_accusative" />
        <paradigm declension="mobile" case="L+I" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="Da" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="G+Abl" form="0e0" footnote="III/IV_pd_genitive-ablative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="Da" form="00e" footnote="III/IV_hd_dative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="G+Abl" form="00o" footnote="II_mobile_genitive-ablative" />
        <paradigm declension="O" case="all" form="00o" footnote="IV/Va_o" />
    </grammar_table>
    <grammar_table id="IV/V (b)" title="Stage IV/V (b): o-stage of ablauts" short_title="stage IV/Vb">
        <description>The o-phase of ablauts (p. 157) starts: Non-accented syllables can ablaut to an o. Since the static inflection uses the former ergative as both nominative and genitive, an un-accented suffix ablaut is introduced in the second for differentiation. An o-grade root is also introduced in o-stems – though Beekes is unclear about its distribution. This stage lies somewhere between stages IV and V in the p. 207 table.</description>
        <declension_def id="static" title="static" short_title="static" />
        <declension_def id="mobile" title="mobile">
            <declension_def id="PD" title="proterodynamic/neuter" short_title="PD (n)" />
            <declension_def id="HD" title="hysterodynamic/animate" short_title="HD (mf)" />
        </declension_def>
        <declension_def id="O" title="o-stems" short_title="O" />
        <case_def id="all" title="all">
            <case_def id="all-but-G" title="all but genitive/ablative">
                <case_def id="N" title="nominative" short_title="nominative" />
                <case_def id="Ac" title="accusative" short_title="accusative" />
                <case_def id="L+I" title="locative, instrumental">
                    <case_def id="L" title="locative" short_title="locative" />
                    <case_def id="I" title="instrumental" short_title="instrumental" />
                </case_def>
                <case_def id="Da" title="dative" short_title="dative" />
            </case_def>
            <case_def id="G+Abl" title="genitive-ablative" short_title="genitive-ablative" />
        </case_def>
        <paradigm declension="static" case="all-but-G" form="e00" footnote="I_static" />
        <paradigm declension="static" case="G+Abl" form="eo0" footnote="IV/Vb_static_genitive" />
        <paradigm declension="mobile" case="N" form="e00" footnote="IV_mobile_nominative" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="Ac" form="e00" footnote="IV_pd_accusative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="Ac" form="0e0" footnote="IV_hd_accusative" />
        <paradigm declension="mobile" case="L+I" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="Da" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="G+Abl" form="0e0" footnote="III/IV_pd_genitive-ablative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="Da" form="00e" footnote="III/IV_hd_dative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="G+Abl" form="00o" footnote="II_mobile_genitive-ablative" />
        <paradigm declension="O" case="all" form="o0o" footnote="IV/Vb_o" />
    </grammar_table>
    <grammar_table id="IV/Vc" title="Stage IV/V (c): static/proterodynamic" short_title="stage IV/Vc">
        <description>The static inflection partly merges with the proterodynamic. This creates a proterodynamic animate inflection (p. 200, 201), with differentiated case endings for nominative (-s) and accusative (-m), and a genitive-ablative influenced in its accent/ablaut class by the static inflection. The static instrumental's zero suffix seems to zero the whole proterodynamic instrumental. This stage lies somewhere between stages IV and V in the p. 207 table.</description>
        <declension_def id="static" title="static" short_title="static" />
        <declension_def id="mobile" title="mobile">
            <declension_def id="PD" title="proterodynamic" short_title="PD">
                <declension_def id="PD_mf" title="proterodynamic/animate" short_title="mf" />
                <declension_def id="PD_n" title="proterodynamic/neuter" short_title="n" />
            </declension_def>
            <declension_def id="HD" title="hysterodynamic" short_title="HD" />
        </declension_def>
        <declension_def id="O" title="o-stems" short_title="O" />
        <case_def id="all" title="all">
            <case_def id="all-but-G" title="all but genitive/ablative">
                <case_def id="N" title="nominative" short_title="nominative" />
                <case_def id="Ac" title="accusative" short_title="accusative" />
                <case_def id="L+I" title="locative, instrumental">
                    <case_def id="L" title="locative" short_title="locative" />
                    <case_def id="I" title="instrumental" short_title="instrumental" />
                </case_def>
                <case_def id="Da" title="dative" short_title="dative" />
            </case_def>
        <case_def id="G+Abl" title="genitive-ablative" short_title="genitive-ablative" />
        </case_def>
        <paradigm declension="static" case="all-but-G" form="e00" footnote="I_static" />
        <paradigm declension="static" case="G+Abl" form="eo0" footnote="IV/Vb_static_genitive" />
        <paradigm declension="mobile" case="N" form="e00" footnote="IV_mobile_nominative" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="Ac" form="e00" footnote="IV_pd_accusative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="Ac" form="0e0" footnote="IV_hd_accusative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="L+I" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="L" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="I" form="?e00" footnote="IV/Vc_pd_instrumental" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="Da" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
        <paradigm declension="PD_mf" case="G+Abl" form="?eo0" footnote="IV/Vc_pd_mf_genitive" />
        <paradigm declension="PD_n" case="G+Abl" form="0e0" footnote="III/IV_pd_genitive-ablative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="Da" form="00e" footnote="III/IV_hd_dative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="G+Abl" form="00o" footnote="II_mobile_genitive-ablative" />
        <paradigm declension="O" case="all" form="o0o" footnote="IV/Vb_o" />
    </grammar_table>
    <grammar_table id="Va" title="Stage V (a): hysterodynamic instrumental" short_title="stage Va">
        <description>The hysterodynamic instrumental follows the genitive and the dative in acquiring a case marker accent, though "perhaps not in all stem classes" (p. 203). The suffix-accented variant cannot have disappeared before the o-stems appeared and took its -h₁ ending, which would afterwards have completely changed to -eh₁. This stage is equal to parts of stage V in the p. 207 table.</description>
        <declension_def id="static" title="static" short_title="static" />
        <declension_def id="mobile" title="mobile">
            <declension_def id="PD" title="proterodynamic" short_title="PD">
                <declension_def id="PD_mf" title="proterodynamic/animate" short_title="mf" />
                <declension_def id="PD_n" title="proterodynamic/neuter" short_title="n" />
            </declension_def>
            <declension_def id="HD" title="hysterodynamic" short_title="HD">
                <declension_def id="HD_A" title="hysterodynamic (some stem classes)" short_title="some" />
                <declension_def id="HD_B" title="hysterodynamic (other stem classes)" short_title="others" />
            </declension_def>
        </declension_def>
        <declension_def id="O" title="o-stems" short_title="O" />
        <case_def id="all" title="all">
            <case_def id="all-but-G" title="all but genitive/ablative">
                <case_def id="N" title="nominative" short_title="nominative" />
                <case_def id="Ac" title="accusative" short_title="accusative" />
                <case_def id="L" title="locative" short_title="locative" />
                <case_def id="I" title="instrumental" short_title="instrumental" />
                <case_def id="Da" title="dative" short_title="dative" />
            </case_def>
        <case_def id="G+Abl" title="genitive-ablative" short_title="genitive-ablative" />
        </case_def>
        <paradigm declension="static" case="all-but-G" form="e00" footnote="I_static" />
        <paradigm declension="static" case="G+Abl" form="eo0" footnote="IV/Vb_static_genitive" />
        <paradigm declension="mobile" case="N" form="e00" footnote="IV_mobile_nominative" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="Ac" form="e00" footnote="IV_pd_accusative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="Ac" form="0e0" footnote="IV_hd_accusative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="L" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
        <paradigm declension="HD_A" case="I" form="0e00e" footnote="Va_hd_instrumental" />
        <paradigm declension="HD_B" case="I" form="00e" footnote="Va_hd_instrumental" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="L" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="I" form="?e00" footnote="IV/Vc_pd_instrumental" />
        <paradigm declension="PD" case="Da" form="0e0" footnote="I_mobile_others" />
        <paradigm declension="PD_mf" case="G+Abl" form="?eo0" footnote="IV/Vc_pd_mf_genitive" />
        <paradigm declension="PD_n" case="G+Abl" form="0e0" footnote="III/IV_pd_genitive-ablative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="Da" form="00e" footnote="III/IV_hd_dative" />
        <paradigm declension="HD" case="G+Abl" form="00o" footnote="II_mobile_genitive-ablative" />
        <paradigm declension="O" case="all" form="o0o" footnote="IV/Vb_o" />
    </grammar_table>
    <forms>
        <form id="e00">é-Ø-Ø</form>
        <form id="0e0">Ø-é-Ø</form>
